#. <section class="sutta" id="mn130"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn130:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 130"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 130"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn130:0.2"
msgid "Devadūtasutta"
msgstr "Messengers of the Gods"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn130:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn130:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn130:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn130:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn130:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.179"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: sadvārā → sandhidvārā (mr)
msgctxt "mn130:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dve agārā sadvārā, tattha cakkhumā puriso majjhe "
"ṭhito passeyya manusse gehaṃ pavisantepi nikkhamantepi anucaṅkamantepi "
"anuvicarantepi;"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, suppose there were two houses with doors. A person with good "
"eyesight standing in between them would see people entering and leaving a "
"house and wandering to and fro."

msgctxt "mn130:2.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena "
"satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate "
"duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi: ‘ime vata bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena "
"samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ "
"anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā; te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā. Ime vā pana bhonto sattā "
"kāyasucaritena samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena "
"samannāgatā ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā; te "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapannā. Ime vata bhonto sattā "
"kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena "
"samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā; te "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapannā. Ime vā pana bhonto sattā "
"kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena "
"samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā; te "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapannā. Ime vā pana bhonto "
"sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā "
"manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā "
"micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā; te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ "
"vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā’ti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I see "
"sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, "
"beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. I understand how "
"sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds. ‘These dear beings did "
"good things by way of body, speech, and mind. They never spoke ill of the "
"noble ones; they had right view; and they chose to act out of that right "
"view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good "
"place, a heavenly realm, or among humans. These dear beings did bad things "
"by way of body, speech, and mind. They spoke ill of the noble ones; they had "
"wrong view; and they chose to act out of that wrong view. When their body "
"breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the ghost realm, the animal realm, "
"or in a lower realm, a bad destination, a world of misery, hell.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā nānābāhāsu gahetvā yamassa rañño dassenti:"
msgstr ""
"Then the wardens of hell take them by the arms and present them to King "
"Yama, saying:"

msgctxt "mn130:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ, deva, puriso amatteyyo apetteyyo asāmañño abrāhmañño, na kule "
"jeṭṭhāpacāyī."
msgstr ""
"‘Your Majesty, this person did not pay due respect to their mother and "
"father, ascetics and brahmins, or honor the elders in the family."

msgctxt "mn130:3.3"
msgid "Imassa devo daṇḍaṃ paṇetū’ti."
msgstr "May Your Majesty punish them!’"

msgctxt "mn130:3.4"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā paṭhamaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjati samanugāhati "
"samanubhāsati:"
msgstr ""
"Then King Yama pursues, presses, and grills them about the first messenger "
"of the gods."

msgctxt "mn130:3.5"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu paṭhamaṃ devadūtaṃ pātubhūtan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see the first messenger of the gods that appeared among "
"human beings?’"

msgctxt "mn130:3.6"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:3.7"
msgid "‘nāddasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw nothing, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:4.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu daharaṃ kumāraṃ mandaṃ "
"uttānaseyyakaṃ sake muttakarīse palipannaṃ semānan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see among human beings a little baby collapsed in their "
"own urine and feces?’"

msgctxt "mn130:4.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:4.4"
msgid "‘addasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw that, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:4.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:4.6"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, tassa te viññussa sato mahallakassa na etadahosi—"
msgstr "‘Mister, did it not occur to you—being sensible and mature—"

msgctxt "mn130:4.7"
msgid ""
"ahampi khomhi jātidhammo, jātiṃ anatīto. Handāhaṃ kalyāṇaṃ karomi kāyena "
"vācāya manasā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"“I, too, am liable to be born. I’m not exempt from rebirth. I’d better do "
"good by way of body, speech, and mind”?’"

msgctxt "mn130:4.8"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:4.9"
msgid "‘nāsakkhissaṃ, bhante, pamādassaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I couldn’t, sir. I was negligent.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.180"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:4.10"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:4.11"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, pamādavatāya na kalyāṇamakāsi kāyena vācāya manasā."
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, because you were negligent, you didn’t do good by way of body, "
"speech, and mind."

msgctxt "mn130:4.12"
msgid "Taggha tvaṃ, ambho purisa, tathā karissanti yathā taṃ pamattaṃ."
msgstr "Well, they’ll definitely punish you to fit your negligence."

#. VAR: pāpakammaṃ → pāpaṃ kammaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn130:4.13"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana te etaṃ pāpakammaṃ neva mātarā kataṃ na pitarā kataṃ na bhātarā "
"kataṃ na bhaginiyā kataṃ na mittāmaccehi kataṃ na ñātisālohitehi kataṃ na "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇehi kataṃ na devatāhi kataṃ, tayāvetaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, "
"tvaññevetassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedissasī’ti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"That bad deed wasn’t done by your mother, father, brother, or sister. It "
"wasn’t done by friends and colleagues, by relatives and kin, by ascetics and "
"brahmins, or by the deities. That bad deed was done by you alone, and you "
"alone will experience the result.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā paṭhamaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjitvā "
"samanugāhitvā samanubhāsitvā dutiyaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjati samanugāhati "
"samanubhāsati:"
msgstr "Then King Yama grills them about the second messenger of the gods."

msgctxt "mn130:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu dutiyaṃ devadūtaṃ pātubhūtan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see the second messenger of the gods that appeared "
"among human beings?’"

msgctxt "mn130:5.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:5.4"
msgid "‘nāddasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw nothing, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:5.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:5.6"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā () jiṇṇaṃ "
"gopānasivaṅkaṃ bhoggaṃ daṇḍaparāyanaṃ pavedhamānaṃ gacchantaṃ āturaṃ "
"gatayobbanaṃ khaṇḍadantaṃ palitakesaṃ vilūnaṃ khalitasiraṃ valinaṃ "
"tilakāhatagattan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see among human beings an elderly woman or a man—"
"eighty, ninety, or a hundred years old—bent double, crooked, leaning on a "
"staff, trembling as they walk, ailing, past their prime, with teeth broken, "
"hair grey and scanty or bald, skin wrinkled, and limbs blotchy?’"

msgctxt "mn130:5.7"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:5.8"
msgid "‘addasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw that, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:5.9"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:5.10"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, tassa te viññussa sato mahallakassa na etadahosi—"
msgstr "‘Mister, did it not occur to you—being sensible and mature—"

msgctxt "mn130:5.11"
msgid ""
"ahampi khomhi jarādhammo, jaraṃ anatīto. Handāhaṃ kalyāṇaṃ karomi kāyena "
"vācāya manasā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"“I, too, am liable to grow old. I’m not exempt from old age. I’d better do "
"good by way of body, speech, and mind”?’"

msgctxt "mn130:5.12"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:5.13"
msgid "‘nāsakkhissaṃ, bhante, pamādassaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I couldn’t, sir. I was negligent.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:5.14"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:5.15"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, pamādavatāya na kalyāṇamakāsi kāyena vācāya manasā."
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, because you were negligent, you didn’t do good by way of body, "
"speech, and mind."

msgctxt "mn130:5.16"
msgid "Taggha tvaṃ, ambho purisa, tathā karissanti yathā taṃ pamattaṃ."
msgstr "Well, they’ll definitely punish you to fit your negligence."

msgctxt "mn130:5.17"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana te etaṃ pāpakammaṃ neva mātarā kataṃ na pitarā kataṃ na bhātarā "
"kataṃ na bhaginiyā kataṃ na mittāmaccehi kataṃ na ñātisālohitehi kataṃ na "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇehi kataṃ na devatāhi kataṃ, tayāvetaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, "
"tvaññevetassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedissasī’ti. (2)"
msgstr ""
"That bad deed wasn’t done by your mother, father, brother, or sister. It "
"wasn’t done by friends and colleagues, by relatives and kin, by ascetics and "
"brahmins, or by the deities. That bad deed was done by you alone, and you "
"alone will experience the result.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.181"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā dutiyaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjitvā samanugāhitvā "
"samanubhāsitvā tatiyaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjati samanugāhati samanubhāsati:"
msgstr "Then King Yama grills them about the third messenger of the gods."

msgctxt "mn130:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu tatiyaṃ devadūtaṃ pātubhūtan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see the third messenger of the gods that appeared among "
"human beings?’"

msgctxt "mn130:6.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:6.4"
msgid "‘nāddasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw nothing, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:6.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:6.6"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā ābādhikaṃ "
"dukkhitaṃ bāḷhagilānaṃ sake muttakarīse palipannaṃ semānaṃ aññehi "
"vuṭṭhāpiyamānaṃ aññehi saṃvesiyamānan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see among human beings a woman or a man, sick, "
"suffering, gravely ill, collapsed in their own urine and feces, being picked "
"up by some and put down by others?’"

msgctxt "mn130:6.7"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:6.8"
msgid "‘addasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw that, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:6.9"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:6.10"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, tassa te viññussa sato mahallakassa na etadahosi—"
msgstr "‘Mister, did it not occur to you—being sensible and mature—"

msgctxt "mn130:6.11"
msgid "ahampi khomhi byādhidhammo, byādhiṃ anatīto."
msgstr ""
"“I, too, am liable to become sick. I’m not exempt from sickness. I’d better "
"do good by way of body, speech, and mind”?’"

msgctxt "mn130:6.12"
msgid "Handāhaṃ kalyāṇaṃ karomi kāyena vācāya manasā’ti? So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:6.13"
msgid "‘nāsakkhissaṃ, bhante, pamādassaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I couldn’t, sir. I was negligent.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:6.14"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:6.15"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, pamādavatāya na kalyāṇamakāsi kāyena vācāya manasā."
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, because you were negligent, you didn’t do good by way of body, "
"speech, and mind."

msgctxt "mn130:6.16"
msgid "Taggha tvaṃ, ambho purisa, tathā karissanti yathā taṃ pamattaṃ."
msgstr "Well, they’ll definitely punish you to fit your negligence."

msgctxt "mn130:6.17"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana te etaṃ pāpakammaṃ neva mātarā kataṃ na pitarā kataṃ na bhātarā "
"kataṃ na bhaginiyā kataṃ na mittāmaccehi kataṃ na ñātisālohitehi kataṃ na "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇehi kataṃ na devatāhi kataṃ, tayāvetaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, "
"tvaññevetassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedissasī’ti. (3)"
msgstr ""
"That bad deed wasn’t done by your mother, father, brother, or sister. It "
"wasn’t done by friends and colleagues, by relatives and kin, by ascetics and "
"brahmins, or by the deities. That bad deed was done by you alone, and you "
"alone will experience the result.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:7.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā tatiyaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjitvā samanugāhitvā "
"samanubhāsitvā catutthaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjati samanugāhati samanubhāsati:"
msgstr "Then King Yama grills them about the fourth messenger of the gods."

msgctxt "mn130:7.2"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu catutthaṃ devadūtaṃ pātubhūtan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see the fourth messenger of the gods that appeared "
"among human beings?’"

msgctxt "mn130:7.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:7.4"
msgid "‘nāddasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw nothing, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:7.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:7.6"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu rājāno coraṃ āgucāriṃ gahetvā "
"vividhā kammakāraṇā kārente—"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see among human beings when the rulers arrested a "
"bandit, a criminal, and subjected them to various punishments—"

msgctxt "mn130:7.7"
msgid ""
"kasāhipi tāḷente vettehipi tāḷente addhadaṇḍakehipi tāḷente hatthampi "
"chindante pādampi chindante hatthapādampi chindante kaṇṇampi chindante "
"nāsampi chindante kaṇṇanāsampi chindante bilaṅgathālikampi karonte "
"saṅkhamuṇḍikampi karonte rāhumukhampi karonte jotimālikampi karonte "
"hatthapajjotikampi karonte erakavattikampi karonte cīrakavāsikampi karonte "
"eṇeyyakampi karonte baḷisamaṃsikampi karonte kahāpaṇikampi karonte "
"khārāpatacchikampi karonte palighaparivattikampi karonte palālapīṭhakampi "
"karonte tattenapi telena osiñcante sunakhehipi khādāpente jīvantampi sūle "
"uttāsente asināpi sīsaṃ chindante’ti?"
msgstr ""
"whipping, caning, and clubbing; cutting off hands or feet, or both; cutting "
"off ears or nose, or both; the ‘porridge pot’, the ‘shell-shave’, the ‘demon’"
"s mouth’, the ‘garland of fire’, the ‘burning hand’, the ‘grass blades’, the "
"‘bark dress’, the ‘antelope’, the ‘meat hook’, the ‘coins’, the ‘acid pickle’"
", the ‘twisting bar’, the ‘straw mat’; being splashed with hot oil, being "
"fed to the dogs, being impaled alive, and being beheaded?’"

msgctxt "mn130:7.8"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:7.9"
msgid "‘addasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw that, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.182"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:7.10"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:7.11"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, tassa te viññussa sato mahallakassa na etadahosi—"
msgstr "‘Mister, did it not occur to you—being sensible and mature—"

#. VAR: kimaṅgaṃ → kimaṅga (bj, s1, pts1)
msgctxt "mn130:7.12"
msgid ""
"ye kira, bho, pāpakāni kammāni karonti te diṭṭheva dhamme evarūpā vividhā "
"kammakāraṇā karīyanti, kimaṅgaṃ pana parattha. Handāhaṃ kalyāṇaṃ karomi "
"kāyena vācāya manasā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"that if someone who does bad deeds receives such punishment in the present "
"life, what must happen to them in the next; I’d better do good by way of "
"body, speech, and mind”?’"

msgctxt "mn130:7.13"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:7.14"
msgid "‘nāsakkhissaṃ, bhante, pamādassaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I couldn’t, sir. I was negligent.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:7.15"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:7.16"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, pamādavatāya na kalyāṇamakāsi kāyena vācāya manasā."
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, because you were negligent, you didn’t do good by way of body, "
"speech, and mind."

msgctxt "mn130:7.17"
msgid "Taggha tvaṃ, ambho purisa, tathā karissanti yathā taṃ pamattaṃ."
msgstr "Well, they’ll definitely punish you to fit your negligence."

msgctxt "mn130:7.18"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana te etaṃ pāpakammaṃ neva mātarā kataṃ na pitarā kataṃ na bhātarā "
"kataṃ na bhaginiyā kataṃ na mittāmaccehi kataṃ na ñātisālohitehi kataṃ na "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇehi kataṃ na devatāhi kataṃ, tayāvetaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, "
"tvaññevetassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedissasī’ti. (4)"
msgstr ""
"That bad deed wasn’t done by your mother, father, brother, or sister. It "
"wasn’t done by friends and colleagues, by relatives and kin, by ascetics and "
"brahmins, or by the deities. That bad deed was done by you alone, and you "
"alone will experience the result.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:8.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā catutthaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjitvā "
"samanugāhitvā samanubhāsitvā pañcamaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjati samanugāhati "
"samanubhāsati:"
msgstr "Then King Yama grills them about the fifth messenger of the gods."

msgctxt "mn130:8.2"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu pañcamaṃ devadūtaṃ pātubhūtan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see the fifth messenger of the gods that appeared among "
"human beings?’"

msgctxt "mn130:8.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:8.4"
msgid "‘nāddasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw nothing, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:8.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:8.6"
msgid ""
"‘ambho purisa, na tvaṃ addasa manussesu itthiṃ vā purisaṃ vā ekāhamataṃ vā "
"dvīhamataṃ vā tīhamataṃ vā uddhumātakaṃ vinīlakaṃ vipubbakajātan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, did you not see among human beings a woman or a man, dead for one, "
"two, or three days, bloated, livid, and festering?’"

msgctxt "mn130:8.7"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:8.8"
msgid "‘addasaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I saw that, sir.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:8.9"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:8.10"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, tassa te viññussa sato mahallakassa na etadahosi—"
msgstr "‘Mister, did it not occur to you—being sensible and mature—"

msgctxt "mn130:8.11"
msgid ""
"ahampi khomhi maraṇadhammo, maraṇaṃ anatīto. Handāhaṃ kalyāṇaṃ karomi kāyena "
"vācāya manasā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"“I, too, am liable to die. I’m not exempt from death. I’d better do good by "
"way of body, speech, and mind”?’"

msgctxt "mn130:8.12"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "mn130:8.13"
msgid "‘nāsakkhissaṃ, bhante, pamādassaṃ, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I couldn’t, sir. I was negligent.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:8.14"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā evamāha:"
msgstr "Then King Yama says:"

msgctxt "mn130:8.15"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, pamādavatāya na kalyāṇamakāsi kāyena vācāya manasā."
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, because you were negligent, you didn’t do good by way of body, "
"speech, and mind."

msgctxt "mn130:8.16"
msgid "Taggha tvaṃ, ambho purisa, tathā karissanti yathā taṃ pamattaṃ."
msgstr "Well, they’ll definitely punish you to fit your negligence."

msgctxt "mn130:8.17"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho pana te etaṃ pāpakammaṃ neva mātarā kataṃ na pitarā kataṃ na bhātarā "
"kataṃ na bhaginiyā kataṃ na mittāmaccehi kataṃ na ñātisālohitehi kataṃ na "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇehi kataṃ na devatāhi kataṃ, tayāvetaṃ pāpakammaṃ kataṃ, "
"tvaññevetassa vipākaṃ paṭisaṃvedissasī’ti. (5)"
msgstr ""
"That bad deed wasn’t done by your mother, father, brother, or sister. It "
"wasn’t done by friends and colleagues, by relatives and kin, by ascetics and "
"brahmins, or by the deities. That bad deed was done by you alone, and you "
"alone will experience the result.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.183"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:9.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, yamo rājā pañcamaṃ devadūtaṃ samanuyuñjitvā "
"samanugāhitvā samanubhāsitvā tuṇhī hoti."
msgstr ""
"Then, after grilling them about the fifth messenger of the gods, King Yama "
"falls silent."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:10.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā pañcavidhabandhanaṃ nāma kammakāraṇaṃ karonti—"
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell punish them with the five-fold crucifixion."

msgctxt "mn130:10.2"
msgid ""
"tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ hatthe gamenti, tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ dutiye hatthe gamenti, "
"tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ pāde gamenti, tattaṃ ayokhilaṃ dutiye pāde gamenti, tattaṃ "
"ayokhilaṃ majjheurasmiṃ gamenti."
msgstr ""
"They drive red-hot stakes through the hands and feet, and another in the "
"middle of the chest."

msgctxt "mn130:10.3"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti."
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:11.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā saṃvesetvā kuṭhārīhi tacchanti … pe …"
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell throw them down and hack them with axes. …"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:12.1"
msgid ""
"tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā uddhampādaṃ adhosiraṃ gahetvā vāsīhi "
"tacchanti … pe …"
msgstr "They hang them upside-down and hack them with hatchets. …"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:13.1"
msgid ""
"tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā rathe yojetvā ādittāya pathaviyā "
"sampajjalitāya sajotibhūtāya sārentipi, paccāsārentipi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"They harness them to a chariot, and drive them back and forth across burning "
"ground, blazing and glowing. …"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:14.1"
msgid ""
"tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā mahantaṃ aṅgārapabbataṃ ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ "
"sajotibhūtaṃ āropentipi oropentipi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"They make them climb up and down a huge mountain of burning coals, blazing "
"and glowing. …"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:15.1"
msgid ""
"tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā uddhampādaṃ adhosiraṃ gahetvā tattāya "
"lohakumbhiyā pakkhipanti ādittāya sampajjalitāya sajotibhūtāya."
msgstr ""
"Then the wardens of hell turn them upside down and throw them in a red-hot "
"copper pot, burning, blazing, and glowing."

msgctxt "mn130:15.2"
msgid "So tattha pheṇuddehakaṃ paccati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn130:15.3"
msgid ""
"So tattha pheṇuddehakaṃ paccamāno sakimpi uddhaṃ gacchati, sakimpi adho "
"gacchati, sakimpi tiriyaṃ gacchati."
msgstr ""
"There they’re seared in boiling scum, and they’re swept up and down and "
"round and round."

msgctxt "mn130:15.4"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti."
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

msgctxt "mn130:15.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā mahāniraye pakkhipanti."
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell toss them into the Great Hell."

msgctxt "mn130:15.6"
msgid "So kho pana, bhikkhave, mahānirayo—"
msgstr "Now, about that Great Hell:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:15.7"
msgid "Catukkaṇṇo catudvāro,"
msgstr "‘Four are its corners, four its doors,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:15.8"
msgid "vibhatto bhāgaso mito;"
msgstr "divided into measured parts."

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:15.9"
msgid "Ayopākārapariyanto,"
msgstr "Surrounded by an iron wall,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:15.10"
msgid "ayasā paṭikujjito."
msgstr "of iron is its roof."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:15.11"
msgid "Tassa ayomayā bhūmi,"
msgstr "The ground is even made of iron,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:15.12"
msgid "jalitā tejasāyutā;"
msgstr "it burns with fierce fire."

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:15.13"
msgid "Samantā yojanasataṃ,"
msgstr "The heat forever radiates"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:15.14"
msgid "pharitvā tiṭṭhati sabbadā."
msgstr "a hundred leagues around.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.184"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:17.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa kho pana, bhikkhave, mahānirayassa puratthimāya bhittiyā acci "
"uṭṭhahitvā pacchimāya bhittiyā paṭihaññati, pacchimāya bhittiyā acci "
"uṭṭhahitvā puratthimāya bhittiyā paṭihaññati, uttarāya bhittiyā acci "
"uṭṭhahitvā dakkhiṇāya bhittiyā paṭihaññati, dakkhiṇāya bhittiyā acci "
"uṭṭhahitvā uttarāya bhittiyā paṭihaññati, heṭṭhā acci uṭṭhahitvā upari "
"paṭihaññati, uparito acci uṭṭhahitvā heṭṭhā paṭihaññati."
msgstr ""
"Now in the Great Hell, flames surge out of the walls and crash into the "
"opposite wall: from east to west, from west to east, from north to south, "
"from south to north, from bottom to top, from top to bottom."

msgctxt "mn130:17.2"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti."
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
#. VAR: apāpurīyati → avāpurīyati (bj)
msgctxt "mn130:18.1"
msgid ""
"Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena "
"tassa mahānirayassa puratthimaṃ dvāraṃ apāpurīyati."
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, the eastern "
"gate of the Great Hell is opened."

msgctxt "mn130:18.2"
msgid "So tattha sīghena javena dhāvati."
msgstr "So they run there as fast as they can."

msgctxt "mn130:18.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa sīghena javena dhāvato chavimpi ḍayhati, cammampi ḍayhati, maṃsampi "
"ḍayhati, nhārumpi ḍayhati, aṭṭhīnipi sampadhūpāyanti, ubbhataṃ tādisameva "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"And as they run, their outer skin, inner skin, flesh, and sinews burn and "
"even their bones smoke. Such is their escape;"

#. VAR: pidhīyati → pithīyati (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn130:18.4"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho so, bhikkhave, bahusampatto hoti, atha taṃ dvāraṃ pidhīyati."
msgstr ""
"but when they’ve managed to make it most of the way, the gate is slammed "
"shut."

msgctxt "mn130:18.5"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti."
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:18.6"
msgid ""
"Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena "
"tassa mahānirayassa pacchimaṃ dvāraṃ apāpurīyati … pe …"
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, the western "
"gate …"

msgctxt "mn130:18.7"
msgid "uttaraṃ dvāraṃ apāpurīyati … pe …"
msgstr "northern gate …"

msgctxt "mn130:18.8"
msgid "dakkhiṇaṃ dvāraṃ apāpurīyati."
msgstr "southern gate of the Great hell is opened."

msgctxt "mn130:18.9"
msgid "So tattha sīghena javena dhāvati."
msgstr "So they run there as fast as they can."

msgctxt "mn130:18.10"
msgid ""
"Tassa sīghena javena dhāvato chavimpi ḍayhati, cammampi ḍayhati, maṃsampi "
"ḍayhati, nhārumpi ḍayhati, aṭṭhīnipi sampadhūpāyanti, ubbhataṃ tādisameva "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"And as they run, their outer skin, inner skin, flesh, and sinews burn and "
"even their bones smoke. Such is their escape;"

msgctxt "mn130:18.11"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho so, bhikkhave, bahusampatto hoti, atha taṃ dvāraṃ pidhīyati."
msgstr ""
"but when they’ve managed to make it most of the way, the gate is slammed "
"shut."

msgctxt "mn130:18.12"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti."
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya19"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:19.1"
msgid ""
"Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayena "
"tassa mahānirayassa puratthimaṃ dvāraṃ apāpurīyati."
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, the eastern "
"gate of the Great Hell is opened."

msgctxt "mn130:19.2"
msgid "So tattha sīghena javena dhāvati."
msgstr "So they run there as fast as they can."

msgctxt "mn130:19.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa sīghena javena dhāvato chavimpi ḍayhati, cammampi ḍayhati, maṃsampi "
"ḍayhati, nhārumpi ḍayhati, aṭṭhīnipi sampadhūpāyanti, ubbhataṃ tādisameva "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"And as they run, their outer skin, inner skin, flesh, and sinews burn and "
"even their bones smoke. Such is their escape;"

msgctxt "mn130:19.4"
msgid "So tena dvārena nikkhamati."
msgstr "and they make it out that door."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya20"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.185"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc30"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:20.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa kho pana, bhikkhave, mahānirayassa samanantarā sahitameva mahanto "
"gūthanirayo."
msgstr "Immediately adjacent to the Great Hell is the vast Dung Hell."

msgctxt "mn130:20.2"
msgid "So tattha patati."
msgstr "And that’s where they fall."

msgctxt "mn130:20.3"
msgid ""
"Tasmiṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, gūthaniraye sūcimukhā pāṇā chaviṃ chindanti, "
"chaviṃ chetvā cammaṃ chindanti, cammaṃ chetvā maṃsaṃ chindanti, maṃsaṃ "
"chetvā nhāruṃ chindanti, nhāruṃ chetvā aṭṭhiṃ chindanti, aṭṭhiṃ chetvā "
"aṭṭhimiñjaṃ khādanti."
msgstr ""
"In that Dung Hell there are needle-mouthed creatures that bore through the "
"outer skin, the inner skin, the flesh, sinews, and bones, until they reach "
"the marrow and devour it."

msgctxt "mn130:20.4"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. (1)"
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:21.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa kho pana, bhikkhave, gūthanirayassa samanantarā sahitameva mahanto "
"kukkulanirayo."
msgstr "Immediately adjacent to the Dung Hell is the vast Hell of Hot Coals."

msgctxt "mn130:21.2"
msgid "So tattha patati."
msgstr "And that’s where they fall."

msgctxt "mn130:21.3"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. (2)"
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya22"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
#. VAR: uddhaṃ → uccaṃ (s1-3, km) | ubbhato (mr)
msgctxt "mn130:22.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa kho pana, bhikkhave, kukkulanirayassa samanantarā sahitameva mahantaṃ "
"simbalivanaṃ uddhaṃ yojanamuggataṃ soḷasaṅgulakaṇṭakaṃ ādittaṃ sampajjalitaṃ "
"sajotibhūtaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Immediately adjacent to the Hell of Hot Coals is the vast Hell of the Red "
"Silk-Cotton Wood. It’s a league high, full of sixteen-inch thorns, burning, "
"blazing, and glowing."

msgctxt "mn130:22.2"
msgid "Tattha āropentipi oropentipi."
msgstr "And there they make them climb up and down."

msgctxt "mn130:22.3"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. (3)"
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya23"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:23.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa kho pana, bhikkhave, simbalivanassa samanantarā sahitameva mahantaṃ "
"asipattavanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Immediately adjacent to the Hell of the Red Silk-Cotton Wood is the vast "
"Hell of the Sword-Leaf Trees."

msgctxt "mn130:23.2"
msgid "So tattha pavisati."
msgstr "They enter that."

msgctxt "mn130:23.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa vāteritāni pattāni patitāni hatthampi chindanti, pādampi chindanti, "
"hatthapādampi chindanti, kaṇṇampi chindanti, nāsampi chindanti, kaṇṇanāsampi "
"chindanti."
msgstr ""
"There the fallen leaves blown by the wind cut their hands, feet, both hands "
"and feet; they cut their ears, nose, both ears and nose."

msgctxt "mn130:23.4"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. (4)"
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
#. VAR: khārodakā nadī → khārodikā nadī (bj)
msgctxt "mn130:24.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa kho pana, bhikkhave, asipattavanassa samanantarā sahitameva mahatī "
"khārodakā nadī."
msgstr ""
"Immediately adjacent to the Hell of the Sword-Leaf Trees is the vast Acid "
"Hell."

msgctxt "mn130:24.2"
msgid "So tattha patati."
msgstr "And that’s where they fall."

msgctxt "mn130:24.3"
msgid ""
"So tattha anusotampi vuyhati, paṭisotampi vuyhati, anusotapaṭisotampi "
"vuyhati."
msgstr ""
"There they are swept upstream, swept downstream, and swept both up and down "
"stream."

msgctxt "mn130:24.4"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti. (5)"
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.186"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:25.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā balisena uddharitvā thale patiṭṭhāpetvā "
"evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr ""
"Then the wardens of hell pull them out and place them on dry land, and say:"

msgctxt "mn130:25.2"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, kiṃ icchasī’ti?"
msgstr "‘Mister, what do you want?’"

msgctxt "mn130:25.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "They say:"

msgctxt "mn130:25.4"
msgid "‘jighacchitosmi, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I’m hungry, sir.’"

msgctxt "mn130:25.5"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā tattena ayosaṅkunā mukhaṃ vivaritvā ādittena "
"sampajjalitena sajotibhūtena tattaṃ lohaguḷaṃ mukhe pakkhipanti ādittaṃ "
"sampajjalitaṃ sajotibhūtaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The wardens of hell force open their mouth with a hot iron spike—burning, "
"blazing, glowing—and shove in a red-hot copper ball, burning, blazing, and "
"glowing."

#. VAR: tassa → tassa (si, pts1) | taṃ tassa (mr)
#. VAR: dahati → ḍayhati (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: urampi → udarampi (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn130:25.6"
msgid ""
"So tassa oṭṭhampi dahati, mukhampi dahati, kaṇṭhampi dahati, urampi dahati, "
"antampi antaguṇampi ādāya adhobhāgā nikkhamati."
msgstr ""
"It burns their lips, mouth, tongue, throat, and stomach before coming out "
"below dragging their entrails."

msgctxt "mn130:25.7"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti."
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya26"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:26.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell say:"

msgctxt "mn130:26.2"
msgid "‘ambho purisa, kiṃ icchasī’ti?"
msgstr "‘Mister, what do you want?’"

msgctxt "mn130:26.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "They say:"

msgctxt "mn130:26.4"
msgid "‘pipāsitosmi, bhante’ti."
msgstr "‘I’m thirsty, sir.’"

msgctxt "mn130:26.5"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā tattena ayosaṅkunā mukhaṃ vivaritvā ādittena "
"sampajjalitena sajotibhūtena tattaṃ tambalohaṃ mukhe āsiñcanti ādittaṃ "
"sampajjalitaṃ sajotibhūtaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The wardens of hell force open their mouth with a hot iron spike—burning, "
"blazing, glowing—and pour in molten copper, burning, blazing, and glowing."

#. VAR: tassa → ettha pana pāṭhabhedo
msgctxt "mn130:26.6"
msgid ""
"Taṃ tassa oṭṭhampi dahati, mukhampi dahati, kaṇṭhampi dahati, urampi dahati, "
"antampi antaguṇampi ādāya adhobhāgā nikkhamati."
msgstr ""
"It burns their lips, mouth, tongue, throat, and stomach before coming out "
"below dragging their entrails."

msgctxt "mn130:26.7"
msgid ""
"So tattha dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedeti, na ca tāva kālaṃ karoti, "
"yāva na taṃ pāpakammaṃ byantīhoti."
msgstr ""
"And there they feel painful, intense, severe, acute feelings—but they don’t "
"die until that bad deed is eliminated."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya27"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:27.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ, bhikkhave, nirayapālā puna mahāniraye pakkhipanti."
msgstr "Then the wardens of hell toss them back in the Great Hell."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya28"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:28.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, yamassa rañño etadahosi:"
msgstr "Once upon a time, King Yama thought:"

msgctxt "mn130:28.2"
msgid ""
"‘ye kira, bho, loke pāpakāni akusalāni kammāni karonti te evarūpā vividhā "
"kammakāraṇā karīyanti."
msgstr ""
"‘Those who do such bad deeds in the world receive these many different "
"punishments."

msgctxt "mn130:28.3"
msgid ""
"Aho vatāhaṃ manussattaṃ labheyyaṃ. Tathāgato ca loke uppajjeyya arahaṃ "
"sammāsambuddho. Tañcāhaṃ bhagavantaṃ payirupāseyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Oh, I hope I may be reborn as a human being! And that a Realized One—a "
"perfected one, a fully awakened Buddha—arises in the world! And that I may "
"pay homage to the Buddha!"

msgctxt "mn130:28.4"
msgid ""
"So ca me bhagavā dhammaṃ deseyya. Tassa cāhaṃ bhagavato dhammaṃ ājāneyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha can teach me Dhamma, so that I may understand his teaching.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya29"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:29.1"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kho panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, nāññassa samaṇassa vā brāhmaṇassa vā sutvā "
"vadāmi, api ca yadeva sāmaṃ ñātaṃ sāmaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sāmaṃ viditaṃ tadevāhaṃ "
"vadāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Now, I don’t say this because I’ve heard it from some other ascetic or "
"brahmin. I only say it because I’ve known, seen, and realized it for myself.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya30"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.187"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:30.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

#. VAR: Idaṃ vatvāna → idaṃ vatvā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn130:30.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:30.3"
msgid "“Coditā devadūtehi,"
msgstr "“Those people who are negligent,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.4"
msgid "ye pamajjanti māṇavā;"
msgstr "when warned by the gods’ messengers:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.5"
msgid "Te dīgharattaṃ socanti,"
msgstr "a long time they sorrow,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.6"
msgid "hīnakāyūpagā narā."
msgstr "when they go to that wretched place."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc40"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:30.7"
msgid "Ye ca kho devadūtehi,"
msgstr "But those good and peaceful people,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.8"
msgid "santo sappurisā idha;"
msgstr "when warned by the gods’ messengers,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.9"
msgid "Coditā nappamajjanti,"
msgstr "never neglect"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.10"
msgid "ariyadhamme kudācanaṃ."
msgstr "the teaching of the noble ones."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc41"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:30.11"
msgid "Upādāne bhayaṃ disvā,"
msgstr "Seeing the danger in grasping,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.12"
msgid "jātimaraṇasambhave;"
msgstr "the origin of birth and death,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.13"
msgid "Anupādā vimuccanti,"
msgstr "they’re freed by not grasping,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.14"
msgid "jātimaraṇasaṅkhaye."
msgstr "with the ending of birth and death."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc42"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:30.15"
msgid "Te khemappattā sukhino,"
msgstr "Happy, they’ve come to a safe place,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.16"
msgid "diṭṭhadhammābhinibbutā;"
msgstr "extinguished in this very life."

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.17"
msgid "Sabbaverabhayātītā,"
msgstr "They’ve gone beyond all threats and perils,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sabbadukkhaṃ → sabbadukkhā (mr)
msgctxt "mn130:30.18"
msgid "sabbadukkhaṃ upaccagun”ti."
msgstr "and risen above all suffering.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn130:30.19"
msgid "Devadūtasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "mn130:30.20"
msgid "Suññatavaggo niṭṭhito tatiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc43"></a>
msgctxt "mn130:30.21"
msgid "Dvidhāva suññatā hoti,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.22"
msgid "Abbhutadhammabākulaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.23"
msgid "Aciravatabhūmijanāmo,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.24"
msgid "Anuruddhupakkilesaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn130:30.25"
msgid "Bālapaṇḍito devadūtañca te dasāti."
msgstr ""
